 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tarqal>Tarqal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#333333>(1/6/03 11:57:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=443.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters Overpowered ?</span><hr size=1> I really dont understand why folks are so adamantly against the nerf of this ability.<br>
<br>
It IS overpowering. Period. You are giving a few classes the ability to handle encounters designed for perhaps 10 to 30 people. Mages having pets that hit for 600 that *May* turn around and kill us is just unreasonable. Can a rogue compete with it? Can a paladin compete with it?  <br>
<br>
Nerf charm, in general. I LOVED charm when I was level 45 with my chanter and would occasionally charm an add as a means of crowd control. It was exciting and also helped the group a lot. Those mobs, however, didnt do 5 or 6 times the damage of my groupmates. New charmed pets do, and I just don't see why you guys wanna defend it.  They specifically stated they were nerfing Manaburn because the ability to do a ton of fast damage with little to no risk trivialized new PoP encounters. How is charm any different?<br>
<br>
I have been on nothing but the beneficial side of charm. I have had druids and chanters helping me kill mobs that I would generally need 20 people to kill to better our odds on winning drops. Charm has directly benefitted me. But, I am willing to acknowledge that I have used it to cut corners and trivialize the new content. I think it is time for that to stop.<br>
<br>
Tarqal<br>
