<br>
You can't feign death or root stuff...<br>
<br>
My cleric can't cast invisibility...<br>
<br>
A Mage at level 65 with ALL his spells and AA's with his Oober pet can outdamage in burst mode 3 Necromancers at level 65..<br>
<br>
All these statements are true.<br>
<br>
Me asking you to refute these would be the same thing.<br>
<br>
At level 64 an Enchanter can charm something that allows them to do MASSIVE damage. Cool.<br>
<br>
There's risk involved, and she can't outdamage 3 of ANY class. In burst output you can find Wizards and Mages do just fine. Charm doesn't eclipse those by any means.<br>
<br>
Charm also has risk.. if you haste that charmed mob, it will one round you when charm breaks.. once charm has broken 3 times the mobs seem to be almost immune to it from then on and you are forced to find another.<br>
<br>
Wizards can quad kite in Halls of Honor.. Bards swarm kite in Plane of Nightmare.. these two methods are faster exp than what chanters can do.<br>
<br>
At level 64 an enchanter that dies 8 times while trying and gets some help from some friends to clear adds, can kill a Dragon that's three expansions old. OMFGS.. can't have that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
