<br>
I have played an enchanter til 32.  That is all, no exp really, I can charm kite and say the exp is great charm kiting and if you give my enchanter a sow/j boots I can charm kite ALL DAY.  But I honestly think charm should be pulled out of the game.  I see no definitive use for it.  You can control the mind of a mob, have it attack something, if it breaks hope you have a healer, or run (in some cases, root, use mez).  Chanters get what, 1500hp rune with PoP?  So add 1500 plus there normal HP, that seems like a lot more than a mage can have when he charms.<br>
<br>
I have read a lot from Jaytee that he dies inevitably when charm breaks, well I can see that because without a pet, we have nothing but gate/run.  Can't stun, root and don't even have a rune, unless you have an item that cast's rune on you.<br>
<br>
really I read these threads a lot and just don't see a reason for charm in the game.  period.  I am a negative thinker normally and really I dont want a class to get nerfed, I just think this route of charming is getting out of hand.  But again this is my own opinion.  If everyone thought the same, message boards would be boring.<br>
<br>
and if you think charm SHOULD be there, then tell me why, I am always open to learning new things.  Don't want to make this post sound like a flame, just my thoughts. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/konno/kass_gif.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
